This Instant Pot Salsa Verde Chicken is one of my go-to methods to prep chicken when I’m feeling lazy to cook but need protein to whip up quick meals during the week. 

In an Instant Pot, place 2 lbs chicken breast and add 3/4 cup salsa verde of your choice plus 1/2 tsp ground cumin. That’s it! Don’t add anything else. The chicken will produce enough liquid as it cooks. 

Cook on manual pressure cooker setting for 15 minutes. Let the Instant Pot slowly release steam gradually. Shred chicken with 2 forks and mix in another 1/4 cup of salsa verde before serving or storing in the fridge. Optional: top with cilantro if desired.

Make this TUNA ONIGIRI with @VitalChoice Ventrasca tuna for a quick and delicious snack.

1 can Ventresca tuna
3 tbsp mayo
2 tbsp furikake 
1 tbsp rice vinegar
1/4 tsp black pepper
2 cups cooked sticky or sushi rice

Combine tuna, mayo, half of the furikake, rice vinegar and black pepper in a bowl. Mix well. 

Wet hands and grab 1/4 cup rice. Place 1 tbsp of tuna mixture in the middle. Cover with another 1/4 cup of rice and roll into a ball then a triangular shape. 

Pan fry each side for 5 minutes on a pan drizzled with a little oil over medium high heat. Sprinkle with remaining furikake. Cool and serve.

Here’s a super easy version of a classic Filipino appetizer called Tokwa’t Baboy (fried tofu and pork) using pork rinds or chicharrones. The tofu cooks perfectly in the air fryer for a dish that’s light and not greasy!

Don’t forget to save this recipe 🙌🏽

1 block firm tofu
1/3 cup coconut aminos* (sub with 1/4 cup low sodium soy sauce if preferred)
1/3 cup cane vinegar
3 Thai chilis 
1/4 cup Red onion, chopped 
1/4 cup scallion sliced 
1 pack (3oz) pork rind with meat

Slice and press tofu between paper towels for 30 mins. 
Cube and cook tofu in air fryer, 400F for 10 mins. 
In a small sauce pan, combine cane vinegar and coconut aminos. Heat up for 2 minutes. 
Place cooked tofu in a large bowl. Add pork rinds, red onion, scallion and Thai chilis. Mix. 
Pour warmed up vinegar and coconut aminos mixture on top. Mix well to evenly distribute sauce.

Serve immediately. 

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere *coconut aminos is from my pantry.

This Instant Pot Chicken Arroz Caldo is comfort food in a bowl. It uses simple ingredients making it a super affordable dish. My go-to toppings are fried garlic, green onions with a splash of calamansi or lemon juice 🙌🏽

2 tbsp diced red onions
2 cloves garlic, minced
2-inch ginger, sliced
1 lb chicken drumettes
1/2 cup jasmine rice, rinsed
2 cups chicken broth
2 1/2 cups water
1/2 tsp sea salt or more to taste 

Toppings:
friend garlic
green onions
calamansi juice 

In an instant pot on Sauté setting, add red onions, ginger and garlic. Cook for 1 minute, until fragrant. 
Add chicken and rice. Mix. 
Pour in broth and water. Mix and cover. 
Cook on Manual setting for 20 minutes.  Once done, let the pressure release naturally. 
Ladle into bowls and top with fried garlic, green onions and calamansi juice. 

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere

Sharing my easy Baked Tahong (Mussels) that I love from childhood. These garlicky and buttery morsels are a fun appetizer!

3 tbsp unsalted butter, softened
5 cloves garlic, minced 
2 lbs cooked mussels
2 tbsp parsley, chopped 

Preheat oven to 375F. 
Place mussels on a parchment lined baking sheet.
Mix butter, garlic and parsley in a bowl. 
Place a small dollop of garlic butter mixture on top of each mussel. 
Bake for 10 mins. 
Serve immediately.

Make this Berry French Toast for One when you‘re craving for something more than just buttered toast. I grabbed a couple slices of cinnamon raisin bread from the freezer and whipped this up in 10 minutes! 

Whisk 1 egg, 2 tbsp milk, 1 tsp ground cinnamon and 1 tsp sugar in a shallow bowl. 
Place 2 slices of bread and flip to coat both sides. Let it sit for a couple of minutes. 
Melt 1 tsp of butter to a pan over medium high heat. 
Place both slices of bread on the pan. Cook for 3-4 minutes until golden brown l. Flip and cool the other side for another 3-4 minutes. 
Transfer to a plate and top with sliced strawberries, blueberries, maple syrup and powdered sugar.

This Coconut Seafood stew (Ginataan) is a typical Filipino dish that’s packed with a ton of flavor. Make this in lieu of a meat dish this Lenten season and enjoy it with a hot bowl of rice🦀🦐 

2 lbs blue crabs
1 lb shrimp
1/2 cup ginger, sliced
1 red onion, diced
1/4 tsp sea salt
1/4 tsp black pepper
2 cans coconut milk
1/4 cup green onions, sliced 

Steam crab first. Place a cup of water in a pot. Add 1/4 cup ginger and bring to a simmer. 

Place blue crabs in the pot, cover and steam for 15-20 minutes. Once cooked, cut in half. 

Using the same pot, remove remaining water and add a little oil. Sauté onion and 1/4 cup ginger for 1 minute over medium high heat. 

Place crabs and shrimp in the pot. Pour coconut milk on top. Season with salt and pepper. Mix and cover. Simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Plate and top with green onions.

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere

This Ube Mango Sticky Rice is so indulgent 🙌🏽 The nuttiness of ube jam compliments the flavors of coconut milk and mangoes making this such a special sweet treat! 

Don’t forget to save this recipe for later 😋

2 cups sweet rice 
3 cups water
2 cans coconut milk
1/2 cup packed brown sugar
1/2 cup Ube jam 
1/4 tsp Ube extract 
2 ripe mangoes 
Toasted sesame seeds for garnish (optional)

Rinse sweet rice until water runs clear. Place rice in a bowl and add water. Let it sit overnight. 

Place a steamer basket on top of a pan with simmering water. Drain soaked sweet rice place it evenly on top of the steamer basket.  Cover and steam for 35 minutes or until rice is cooked. 

In a small saucepan, add coconut milk and brown sugar. Bring to a simmer and cook until it begins to thicken. 

Place cooked rice on a bowl and mix in ube jam and half of the coconut sauce. Add ube extract. Mix well. Let it sit for an hour. 

Scoop sticky rice on a place and serve with sliced mangoes, extra coconut sauce and toasted sesame seeds. 

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere

Giniling or Filipino Picadillo is a simple and savory family friendly recipe that is ready in 30 minutes. Perfect for a busy weeknight meal! 

1 tbsp cooking oil of choice
4 cloves garlic, minced
1 carrot, cubed
2 red potatoes, cubed
2 lbs ground beef
1 bell pepper, cubed
1 15oz can tomato sauce 
1/2 cup coconut aminos 
Sant and pepper to taste 

Sauté garlic, carrots and potato in a little oil for 2-3 mins. Remove and set aside. 
Add beef. Cook until it begins to brown. 
Add coconut aminos and tomato sauce. 
Add carrots, potatoes and bell pepper. Stir and simmer for 20 minutes. 
Serve over steamed rice.

Turn simple ingredients into an extraordinary dish with this garlicky, savory Beef Salpicao (Filipino Stir Fry Beef) that’s reminiscent of your Lola’s home cooking. 😋🇵🇭

Beef Salpicao Recipe
2 tbsp oil of your choice 
6 garlic cloves, minced 
2 lbs ribeye steak or top sirloin 
1/4 tsp sea salt 
1/4 tsp black pepper
1/4 cup coconut aminos 
2 tbsp Worcestershire sauce 
3 tbsp unsalted butter 

Cook garlic over low heat until browned, about 2-3 minutes. Remove and set aside. 

Add beef to the pan and season with salt and pepper. Cook for a few minutes until it begins to brown.

Season beef with coconut aminos and Worcestershire sauce. Stir, cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes until beef is tender. 

Add butter and fried garlic then mix and cook uncovered until liquid has evaporated.

✨New Recipe - Homemade Taho Made Easy ✨ Sweet and filling Taho is one of my childhood favorite snacks when I was growing up in the Philippines. 

April is Filipino Food month so I’ll be sharing recipes from my motherland to help bring more awareness and appreciation of my culture’s culinary heritage.

Taho
1/2 cup small sago pearls 
3 1/3 cups water
2/3 cup coconut sugar (or dark brown sugar)
1 block silken tofu 

Boil 3 cups water and add sago pearls. Cook for 10-15 minutes, stirring constantly so it doesn’t clump up. Drain, rinse and set aside.

Prepare the arnibal (caramelized sugar syrup) by combining the remaining 1/3 cup water and coconut sugar in a pot. Simmer for 5-8 minutes until it begins to thicken. 

Place silken tofu on a steam basket and steam for 15 minutes until cooked through. 

Alternately scoop silken tofu, sago pearls and arnibal in a cup and enjoy immediately.

Nilagang Baka or boiled beef is one of the easiest Filipino dishes that’s tasty, nourishing and comforting. It’s a one pot complete meal filled with vegetables, tender meat (thanks to the Instant Pot) and filling carbs. 

Instant Pot Beef Nilaga 🍲
2 lbs beef short ribs 
1 red onion, quartered 
5 cups water
1 tbsp peppercorn
fish sauce to taste 
1 carrot, sliced
1 russet potatoes, cubed
1 corn, cut into 4 pieces 
1 pack baby bokchoy

1.) Place beef, onion, water and peppercorn in the Instant Pot. 
2.) Cook on Stew setting for 45 mins. 
3.) Use the quick release method by turning the steam release handle to venting.
4.) Skim any impurities that float to the top. 5.) Season with fish sauce to taste. 
6.) Add carrot, corn, potato and cook for 5-8 minutes until tender. 
7.) Add baby bokchoy and cook for 2 more minutes. 
8.) Serve hot.

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere

These soy-free🥚Marinated Soft Boiled Eggs 🥚 are delicious on its own or as a quick meal with rice topped with furikake, bonito flakes and chili crunch. 😋

6 large eggs*
3/4 cup coconut aminos
1/4 cup rice vinegar 
2 cloves garlic, minced
1/4 tsp sea salt 
Topping: furikake, bonito, chili crunch 

*Make sure eggs are at room temperature before cooking. 

Boil eggs for 6 minutes. 

Transfer to an ice bath to cool. Peel and place in a bowl. 

Combine coconut aminos, rice vinegar, minced garlic and salt and mix well. Pour sauce over the eggs, cover and store in the fridge overnight. 

Serve over rice topped with furikake, bonito and chili crunch. 

#marinatedeggs #soyfree #glutenfree #easysnack #quickmeal @thehappyeggco #foodstagram #reelvideo #reelinstagram

This 4 ingredient 🥭Mango Float🥭 dessert is a dairy free, lightened up version that will take you back to the tropics. It’s a no bake treat so it’s super easy and fun to make. 

Recipe:
4 ripe mangoes
2 cans full fat coconut milk, chilled in the fridge overnight 
1/2 cup honey
approx 27 pieces graham crackers

1.) Scoop chilled coconut cream from the can and place in a bowl. Using a stand or hand mixer, whip until it becomes fluffy. About 3-4 minutes.
2.) Add honey and gently fold into the whipped coconut cream. 
3.) Cut and slice  mangoes into strips. 
4.) In a rectangular Pyrex dish, place 9 pieces of graham crackers side by side. 
5.)Spread about 3/4 cup of whipped coconut cream. Make sure to cover every piece of graham cracker. 
6.) Place sliced mangoes on top of the cream. 
7.) Repeat steps 4-6 a couple more times.
8.) Crush some graham crackers and sprinkle on top of the mango float. 
9.) Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 8 hours - overnight. 
10.) Enjoy the next day.

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere

Pork Humba 🐷 is a one pot savory and slightly sweet dish similar to Filipino Adobo. This is my shortcut version that uses pork hocks but it can also be easily made with pork belly. So good with lots of white rice! 🍚

Recipe:
5 garlic cloves, minced 
1 red onion, chopped 
3 lbs pork hock pata pieces/pork belly
2/3 cup coconut aminos 
2/3 cup vinegar 
1 pineapple juice can 
2 bay leaves
1 tbsp whole peppercorn 
1 tsp sea salt 
1 pack dried banana flowers 

Saute garlic, onion until slightly translucent. Add pork, coconut aminos, vinegar, pineapple juice, salt, pepper, banana flowers and bay leaf in the pan. Simmer covered for 60- 75 mins until pork is tender. 

All ingredients are from my neighborhood @islandpacificmarket #PresyongSulit #SarapStartsHere (coconut aminos is from my pantry)

✨New Recipe✨ This One Pot Chicken and Rice made easy with pantry ready ingredients is a no-fuss, family friendly meal. 

3 cups rice
2 cups chicken broth
1 1/2 cups water 
4 stalks green onions, sliced
2 inch ginger, sliced 
3 lbs chicken thighs, boneless, skinless 
1/4 cup coco aminos
2 tsp sesame oil
1 tsp sea salt

Drizzling Sauce: 
1/4 cup coconut aminos
1 tbsp oyster sauce 
1 tbsp fried garlic 

Place rinsed jasmine rice in an instant pot. Add chicken broth, water, green onions and ginger. 

Season chicken thighs with coconut aminos, sesame oil and salt. Mix well. Let it marinate for 5 minutes. 

Place chicken on top of the rice in the instant pot. Cover and cook on manual setting for 25 minutes. Allow pressure to naturally release. 

Prepare the drizzling sauce by combining coconut aminos, oyster sauce and fried garlic in a bowl. Let it sit for 5-10 minutes until the garlic is soft. 

Serve chicken and rice with sauce. 

#chickenandrice #onepotmeal #weeknightmeal #instantpotmeals

Here’s a homemade version of Pork Siomai, a traditional Chinese dumpling adapted for the Filipino palate. Make and steam some now and save half for later when the Pork Siomai craving hits! 

Recipe:
1 carrot
1 cup shiitake mushroom
3 stalks green onions
1 pound shrimp
1.5 pounds ground pork
2 large eggs
2 tbsp cornstarch 
1 1/2 tsp black pepper
2 tsp sea salt
1 pack siomai wrapper

Dipping sauce:
calamansi or lemon juice 
coconut aminos 
chili oil 

Finely chop carrot, shiitake mushroom, green onions and shrimp. Place in a large bowl. 

Add ground pork, eggs, cornstarch, pepper and salt. Mix well. 

Place 2 tbsp of meat in the middle of a siomai wrapper. Wet edges with water and pinch the sides until it forms a tiny cup. Repeat with the remaining mixture. 

Steam for 20-25 minutes. 

Serve with equal parts of calamansi (or lemon) and coconut aminos and a little bit of chili oil.

#CampbellsPartner Here’s a Creamy Veggie version of a Filipino side dish that is served during special occasions or holidays. It’s a quick and easy side dish that’s ready in less than 20 minutes thanks to Campbell’s® Condensed Cream of Mushroom Soup to achieve a rich, creamy texture that’s full of delicious flavor. 

Recipe:
1 tbsp butter
3 cloves garlic, minced
1/2 cup chopped onion
1 pine of stir fry vegetables (mushrooms, bell peppers, carrots, celery, cabbage, squash and zucchini)
1/2 cup milk
1 can Campbell’s® Condensed Cream of Mushroom Soup
1 tsp fish sauce (sub with 1 tsp sea salt)
1 tsp ground black pepper 

Melt butter in a pan over medium high heat. 
Add garlic and onions. Sauté until softened, about 2 mins. 
Add vegetables. Sauté for 5 minutes until half cooked. 

Pour milk and add a can of Campbell’s® Condensed Cream of Mushroom Soup. Stir and simmer for 5-8 minutes. 
Season with fish sauce (or salt) and black pepper. Simmer for 2 more minutes. 
Remove from heat and serve.

My Creamiest Mashed Potato Recipe is super easy and makes the best side dish to any holiday meal ✨

I use a potato ricer which is one of the best kitchen gadgets I’ve ever bought because it mashes potatoes like a dream! Mascarpone has a rich and buttery flavor that adds a decadent touch to these ultra creamy potatoes. 

8 pounds Yukon gold potatoes
6 tbsp salted butter, cubed
3/4 cup milk
8oz tub Mascarpone cheese*
Sea salt to taste 

1. Peel and quarter potatoes.
2. Place in a pot and add water until potatoes are covered. 
3. Bring to a boil and cook potatoes until fork tender, about 10-15 minutes. 
4. Drain and mash potatoes using a potato ricer or masher. 
5. Stir in butter, milk and Mascarpone cheese
6. Season with salt. 
7. Mix well until light and fluffy. 

*can sub with cream cheese but I highly recommend Mascarpone because it’s so worth it!
